      "comment": {
        "comments": [
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12748359/comment/15425272",
            "id": "15425272",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe",
              "name": "jlowe",
              "key": "jlowe",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Jason Darrell Lowe",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Chicago"
            },
            "body": "We've run into a number of situations where the lack of reservations-continue-looking support for labelled nodes has caused problems, so it would be good to get some traction on this.  Attaching a patch that is a port to trunk of what we've been running on our 2.7 release.  It simply turns off the \"only for unlabelled nodes\" checks for the feature.\n\nI think this works fine for something like 2.7 with exclusive labels.  When it goes looking for another reservation to release it will be a reservation against the same label.  For non-exclusive labels this simplistic approach may not be sufficient.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe",
              "name": "jlowe",
              "key": "jlowe",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
